<a name="lists">
<h2>
Mailing lists
</h2>
<p>
There are currently two PyXPlot mailing lists.  <a href="http://www.srcf.ucam.org/mailman/listinfo/pyxplot-announce">pyxplot-announce</a>
is a low-volume moderated list for announcement of new PyXPlot releases.  <a
href="http://www.srcf.ucam.org/mailman/listinfo/pyxplot-user">pyxplot-user</a>
is a higher-volume unmoderated list for discussion; any list member can post to it.  To sign up for one of these lists please visit the linked pages.

<a name="bugs">
<h2>
Bugs
</h2>
<p>
There is a <a href="bugs_noauth/trac.cgi">bug tracking system</a>, which is
currently read-only. If you have a Cambridge University raven account, you
should <a href="http://www.srcf.ucam.org/pyxplot/bugs/trac.cgi">click here</a>
for a read-write access. The author would be very pleased to receive bug
reports from other users emailed to <a
href="mailto:coders@pyxplot.org.uk">Dominic Ford</a>.
</p>


